  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have legal frameworks to combat money laundering. Some key elements include:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Regulatory Mechanisms:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Bank reporting obligations\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n\n4. Enforcement Actions:\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Significant financial penalties\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Compliance Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement internal control systems\n- Regular risk assessments\n- Staff training on detecting suspicious activities\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute money laundering activities across different sectors and jurisdictions.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
